# You normally DON'T need this. When you run `npm start` (or `npm run play`), the
# game server serves the app and the WebSocket from the same place, so the client
# connects same-origin automatically — local play and tunnels just work.
#
# Set VITE_WS_HOST only when the frontend is served separately from the game
# server (e.g. Vite dev on :5173 talking to the server on :1999, or a statically
# hosted frontend pointing at a server elsewhere). Examples:
#   VITE_WS_HOST=127.0.0.1:1999
#   VITE_WS_HOST=your-machine.example.com
VITE_WS_HOST=
